Brazil May Use Reserves to Purchase Assets Abroad, Estado Says

-- B y   I u r i   D a n t a s
-- 
2011-05-24T11:59:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/brazil-may-use-reserves-to-purchase-assets-abroad-estado-says.html
The Brazilian government may use its
foreign reserves to purchase assets abroad, O Estado de S.Paulo
newspaper  reported , without saying how it obtained the
information.  The government may use its $331 billion in foreign reserves
in conjunction with the state development bank, known as BNDES,
to purchase assets sought by Brazilian companies outside the
country, the newspaper said.  A spokesman for Brazilian central bank wasnâ€™t immediately
